The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 New home for Japan GP

Tokyo: The Japanese Formula One Grand Prix will take place at Fuji Speedway in 2007, circuit owner Toyota said on Friday. The track replaces the Suzuka international circuit, which is owned by rival Japanese car manufacturer Honda and has hosted the race since 1987. 

We have the pleasure (to announce) that Fuji Speedway... will be the new home of Japanese F1 Grand Prix, F1 chief Bernie Ecclestone said in the statement. (REUTERS) 




